<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-716-047  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 716 047.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Dec 17 1990 n399 p24(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM plans support-analysis program. (IBM Business Consultingprogram performs comprehensive analysis of a computer resellersservice and support operations for a fee)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hedlund, Kristen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>IBM's forthcoming IBM Business Consulting program will perform acomprehensive analysis of a computer reseller's support andservice operations for a fee reimbursable through IBM's ProPlan.andO;The central goal of the program is to improve the profitability ofthe support and service aspects of the dealers' business.andP;  An IBMsurvey of 200 dealers determined that service revenues contributed30 to 40 percent of the dealers' profitability from only 7 to 10percent of total sales.andP;  Unfortunately, the support and servicecapabilities of dealers were highly variable.andP;  Some dealers werenot managing their service operations well and even losing money.andO;A pilot of the Business Consulting program was very successful.andO;The program will debut on a limited basis in 1st qtr 1991.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (Services).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     Support ServicesManufacturersComputer IndustryComputer RetailingProduct IntroductionPerformance ImprovementGoals and ObjectivesAnalysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>